Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.58,0:00:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Our text is focusing \Non the powerful effect \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.69,0:00:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that prayer can have on us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.86,0:00:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,when it is true prayer, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.76,0:00:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,genuine prayer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.30,0:00:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Mere communication with God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.07,0:00:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,is not necessarily prayer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.20,0:00:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,In Genesis \Nchapters 3 and 4, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.27,0:00:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,after Adam had sinned, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.31,0:00:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,he had dialogue with Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.78,0:00:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but it could hardly \Nbe viewed as prayer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.01,0:00:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.61,0:00:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Because prayer involves trust, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.35,0:00:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,respect, humility, devotion, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.19,0:00:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and a sense of dependence \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.26,0:00:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,on the one to whom \Nthe prayer is directed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.93,0:00:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, just to highlight \Nthe importance of trust \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.53,0:00:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and prayer’s effectiveness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.40,0:00:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s open our Bibles \Nto Psalm 91, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.37,0:00:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’ll see the important quality \Nof trust highlighted. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.94,0:00:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Psalm 91, \Nwe’ll read verses 1 and 2. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.54,0:01:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“Anyone dwelling in the secret place \Nof the Most High \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.31,0:01:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,will lodge under the shadow \Nof the Almighty.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.48,0:01:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we notice “the secret place,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.39,0:01:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,a place of spiritual security \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.36,0:01:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,where no one or no thing \Ncan rob us of our faith in Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.89,0:01:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,or our love for Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.90,0:01:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s secret because unbelievers \Ncan’t understand it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.37,0:01:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, \Nhow do we get there? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.50,0:01:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 2: \N“I will say to Jehovah: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.77,0:01:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,‘You are my refuge \Nand my stronghold, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.41,0:01:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,my God in whom I trust.’” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.05,0:01:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So the key of getting \Ninto the secret place, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.35,0:01:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the key to getting \Nthe peace of God, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.22,0:01:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is this humility \Nand trust in Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.56,0:01:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And we notice \Nthe expression here: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.56,0:01:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“You are my refuge \Nand my stronghold.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.23,0:01:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In this context, not ours\N—while it’s true—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.40,0:02:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but it has to be personal. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.07,0:02:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s the trust \Nthat we have on an individual basis.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.57,0:02:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And how grateful we are \Nthat we have Jehovah’s listening ear, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.34,0:02:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and he hears us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.45,0:02:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,because of something \Nthat David said. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.58,0:02:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We go to Psalm 69 this time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.92,0:02:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and as we turn here, \Nwe’d like to ask you to think, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.59,0:02:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,“Have you ever felt, \Nto a reasonable degree, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.39,0:02:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the same way that David \Nexpresses himself here?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.16,0:02:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s going through \Na very stressful time, overwhelmed, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.53,0:02:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and in verse 20 of Psalm 69, \Nhe says:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.74,0:02:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“Reproach has broken my heart, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.27,0:02:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the wound is incurable. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.38,0:02:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“I was hoping for sympathy, \Nbut there was none,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.01,0:02:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and for comforters, \Nbut I found none.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.45,0:02:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So at times, \Nour fellow believers\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.59,0:02:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,—our family members even, \Nclose friends—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.19,0:02:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,they may not be able to help us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.53,0:02:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the way we need to be helped. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.53,0:03:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And why is that? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.53,0:03:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, for one thing, they may be \Nvery busy dealing with their own problems, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.90,0:03:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and they don’t have \Nthe time to really notice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.54,0:03:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Or the other factor is \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.77,0:03:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that we all have things that differ \Nwhen it comes to causing us stress. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.34,0:03:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What is a real stress for one person \Nis not so hard for another. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.65,0:03:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And if they look on \Nand see someone \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.32,0:03:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,going through something \Nthat they find easy, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.99,0:03:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps the sympathy will be lacking.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.32,0:03:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But, nonetheless, \Nverse 33 of this same Psalm says:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.46,0:03:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“For Jehovah \Nis listening to the poor, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.50,0:03:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and he will not despise \Nhis captive people.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.13,0:03:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in principle, \Nsometimes we may feel captive \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.37,0:03:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to our circumstances \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.47,0:03:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,or to the feelings \Nthat we’re experiencing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.57,0:03:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to our emotions, \Nto what we are going through\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.88,0:03:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,—we feel trapped. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.88,0:03:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Other people may not understand \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.45,0:03:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,or may not be able to help us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.52,0:03:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But notice the reassurance \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.15,0:04:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in 2 Chronicles 6:29, 30. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.09,0:04:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the prayer of Solomon \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.46,0:04:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time \Nof the dedication of the temple. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.83,0:04:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And in 2 Chronicles 6:29 \Nhe says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.50,0:04:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“Whatever request for favor \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.60,0:04:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“may be made by any man \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.60,0:04:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“or by all your people Israel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.17,0:04:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“(for each one knows \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.31,0:04:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“his own plague and his own pain)\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.31,0:04:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,when they spread out \Ntheir hands toward this house,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.05,0:04:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,so we’re unique. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.05,0:04:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Other people may not be able to do it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.85,0:04:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? \NVerse 30: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.45,0:04:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then may you hear\Nfrom the heavens, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.46,0:04:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“your dwelling place, \Nand may you forgive; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.86,0:04:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“and reward each one \Naccording to all his ways, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.00,0:04:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“for you know his heart \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.06,0:04:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“(you alone truly know \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.90,0:04:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the human heart).” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.97,0:04:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So even if our friends care, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.57,0:04:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,even if they want to be helpful, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.94,0:04:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,they cannot possibly see \Nthe depth of what we’re feeling \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.05,0:04:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,or what we’re thinking \Nor how it’s affecting us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.45,0:05:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jehovah does. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.65,0:05:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He sees right \Nto the heart of the matter, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.25,0:05:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and how reassuring that is. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.89,0:05:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So we trust him \Nbecause he really knows us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.13,0:05:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But there’s something else \Ninvolved in this trust. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.37,0:05:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Matthew 6:33 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.67,0:05:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“Keep on, then, seeking first \Nthe Kingdom and his righteousness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.61,0:05:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and all these other things \Nwill be added to you.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.08,0:05:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, there’s personal trust\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.95,0:05:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,—trust that Jehovah \Nknows what I need \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.25,0:05:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and that he’s going to, \Nas he always has, provide it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.52,0:05:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But there can be a pitfall. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.56,0:05:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If a person \Nis naturally calm, confident, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.86,0:05:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps has a natural ability, \Nfamily history that’s rich\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.80,0:05:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,—both emotionally, \Nmaybe even financially—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.20,0:05:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,all of these things \Ncan make a person begin to feel, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.67,0:06:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Yes, I trust in Jehovah, \Nbut I can do this myself.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.85,0:06:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, sometimes \Nwe may hear this expression \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.08,0:06:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,when we hear of someone \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.32,0:06:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that’s being transitioned \Nfrom one form of special service, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.05,0:06:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps into \Nthe regular pioneer work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.06,0:06:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,or they have to leave Bethel \Nfor good reasons, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.12,0:06:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and they have to go back \Nand get some secular work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.19,0:06:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever heard this? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.46,0:06:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“They’re going to do fine \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.67,0:06:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,because they have marketable skills.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.24,0:06:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, \Nthat’s a good thing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.24,0:06:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps those marketable skills \Nhave been developed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.41,0:06:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in pursuing Kingdom interests, \Nand that’s fine. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.78,0:06:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But we have to be careful. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.28,0:06:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Will they be fine \Nbecause of their skills \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.68,0:06:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,or because of their continuing \Nto seek first the Kingdom \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.02,0:06:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and they let Jehovah \Nbe the one that provides for them? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.29,0:06:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’ll have to be careful too \Nwhen we use that expression\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.46,0:06:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“They’ll have no problem; \Nthey have marketable skills.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.20,0:06:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What if someone doesn’t? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.30,0:06:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Jehovah \Ntakes care of them too. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.14,0:07:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Amos 7:14, 15, \NAmos said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.77,0:07:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I wasn’t a prophet \Nor the son of a prophet. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.74,0:07:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a nipper of figs, \Na very lowly herdsman, shepherd.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.78,0:07:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah took him, \Nused him, and provided for him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.38,0:07:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So marketable skills \Nwere not the key factor. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.65,0:07:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we keep that \Nin its proper perspective.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.46,0:07:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, \Nin imitation of Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.33,0:07:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,when we try to help people, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.33,0:07:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to use the most powerful tool \Nwe have to encourage them\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.70,0:07:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and to help them deal \Nwith their anxiety. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.20,0:07:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There was an experience \Nin the February 15, 1988, Watchtower \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.07,0:07:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,about Brother Arthur Winkler. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.28,0:07:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, \Nthe Gestapo found him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.38,0:07:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and they beat him \Nwithout mercy, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.38,0:07:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,knocked out his teeth, \Ndislocated his jaw. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.85,0:07:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,His whole body \Nwas raw from the beating, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.22,0:07:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and they threw him in a dark cell. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.59,0:07:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,At that moment, \NBrother Winkler said, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.76,0:08:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“I was in desperate need \Nof spiritual food, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.03,0:08:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and I prayed to Jehovah.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.47,0:08:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he talked to the guard \Nand asked him to help him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.04,0:08:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The cell door opened \Nand a Bible was thrown in, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.87,0:08:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and he said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.91,0:08:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“That daily enjoyment \Nof those pleasant words of truth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.01,0:08:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“were precious. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.05,0:08:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt myself \Ngetting stronger spiritually.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.32,0:08:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So, then, \Nwhen we go to help people, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.35,0:08:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the best thing we can do \Nin helping them cope is, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.46,0:08:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,not with some \Noften-used phrase \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.19,0:08:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,or something that is \Nrepeatable all the time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.66,0:08:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,but make sure it is the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.87,0:08:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They may feel captive, \Nimprisoned by their situation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.97,0:08:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But an account from the Bible\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.14,0:08:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,—an account of a Bible character \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.17,0:08:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that had gone through tough times \Nand came through—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.61,0:08:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,those are the most meaningful things \Nto deal with it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.31,0:08:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps \N2 Corinthians 11:23-31, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.98,0:08:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,where Paul reviewed\Nall of those things that he went through, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.35,0:09:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet years later, \Nhe wrote our day’s text for today, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.26,0:09:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,saying Jehovah helped him \Nstay calm and assisted him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.79,0:09:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So may these reminders \Nfrom the Scriptures \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.93,0:09:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,help us to cope and help others \Nto cope with anxieties.\N
